# ------------------------------- start overview ------------------------------- # 
    ==> Quick View: a Flash parameter injection vulnerability occures when:
                    - the attacker can insert malicious code into the web application.
                    - the web application passes the input provided by the attacker to the flash animation without any
                    significant sanitization.
                    - the flash animation, embedded in the html page, does not sanitize input parameters.

    ==> flash parameter injection could be vulnerable to XSS, example of payload site=javascript:alert('test');

    # ---------- |tools| ---------- #
        - SWFinvestigator
            - contains a fuzzer that searches for XSS vulnerability.
# -------------------------------   end overview ------------------------------- # 
